                            <comment id="136843" author="pjones" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2015 13:34:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok great. So let&apos;s close this ticket as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7144&quot; title=&quot;Interop 2.7.0&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;master- sanity-scrub test_14: (6) Some entry under /lost+found should be repaired&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7144&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7144&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and reopen if it is hit with that fix in place&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="136826" author="emoly.liu" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2015 08:20:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;By searching recent 4 weeks maloo testing results on zfs, I found before this error happened, sanity-scrub.sh was skipped, 100%. And before skipping, sanity-scrub always reformats ost&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1-4&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, I think that is why &quot;no label for lustre-ost5&quot; was reported later.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just checked sanity-scrub.sh and found this issue was fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7144&quot; title=&quot;Interop 2.7.0&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;master- sanity-scrub test_14: (6) Some entry under /lost+found should be repaired&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7144&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7144&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/17520/4/lustre/tests/sanity-scrub.sh&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/17520/4/lustre/tests/sanity-scrub.sh&lt;/a&gt;), landed on Dec.14th.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, please update the code to include the fix and see if this error still exists.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="136736" author="sarah" created="Thu, 17 Dec 2015 17:49:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Emoly,&lt;br/&gt;
Yes, this only affects zfs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
